27
00:02:31,647 --> 00:02:33,205
Okay. What is it?

28
00:02:45,527 --> 00:02:47,324
He taught me a song for his birthday.

29
00:02:47,487 --> 00:02:51,605
I have to sing it for him tonight
at bedtime, and I can't think what it is.

30
00:02:51,767 --> 00:02:54,076
Sing a little more and we'll figure it out.

31
00:03:13,247 --> 00:03:14,521
What the hell was that?

32
00:03:15,647 --> 00:03:18,320
- Oh, my God!
- Call 911!

33
00:03:19,967 --> 00:03:22,561
<i>- 911.</i>
- I want to report a shooting.

34
00:03:31,407 --> 00:03:34,763
- Get behind the desk and stay there!
<i>- Ma 'am?</i>

35
00:03:34,927 --> 00:03:36,963
The Laurel Morgan Building.

36
00:03:37,127 --> 00:03:38,879
- Third floor.
<i>- How many are injured?</i>

37
00:03:39,047 --> 00:03:42,244
I don't know. I don't know
how many... No, stay with me!

38
00:03:42,527 --> 00:03:45,360
- God! They put me on hold. Hello?
- Oh, shit.

39
00:03:46,047 --> 00:03:48,436
- Come on, somebody...
- Calm down.

40
00:03:48,607 --> 00:03:51,883
- Can you see anything?
- It'll be fine. I promise.

41
00:03:52,087 --> 00:03:53,566
Hello?

42
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:56,000
Hello?

43
00:04:02,887 --> 00:04:05,959
Come on.
Please send somebody.

44
00:04:07,647 --> 00:04:10,036
Pick up. Please pick up.

45
00:04:44,007 --> 00:04:47,363
- Good morning, Mr. Pulaski.
- Morning, Nick.

46
00:04:48,767 --> 00:04:50,280
Need some help with that?

47
00:04:50,447 --> 00:04:54,201
The bilge ring keeps crapping out,
blocking up the damn pump. I got it.

48
00:04:54,367 --> 00:04:57,040
Last time you nearly took out
every sink in the Quarter.

49
