00:22:18,207 --> 00:22:19,879
Well, thank you all for being here.

341
00:22:20,047 --> 00:22:21,685
Thank you, Jim.

342
00:22:22,087 --> 00:22:24,442
- Mr. Docken.
- Yes, sir.

343
00:22:24,607 --> 00:22:26,723
- How do you do?
- Fine, thank you.

344
00:22:27,007 --> 00:22:29,760
<i>How do you feel about</i>
<i>being a juror in this trial?</i>

345
00:22:30,207 --> 00:22:33,404
<i>- Do you feel you could be fair...</i>
- Look at how he's hunched <i>over...</i>

346
00:22:33,567 --> 00:22:36,877
...and his fingers are interlaced.
He's trying not to be too obvious.

347
00:22:37,047 --> 00:22:39,481
He's definitely on our side
of the fence.

348
00:22:39,647 --> 00:22:42,684
It's a veneer. He's campaigning.
He wants on. Bounce him.

349
00:22:42,847 --> 00:22:46,362
- We're almost out of challenges.
- I don't care. Bounce him!

350
00:22:47,967 --> 00:22:50,606
- Peremptory challenge.
- Hold on, hear me out.

351
00:22:50,767 --> 00:22:52,200
<i>Thank you, you're excused.</i>

352
00:22:52,367 --> 00:22:54,358
- I wanna be heard.
