come back asking for more.

370
00:24:01,087 --> 00:24:03,806
A total of 12 million more.

371
00:24:03,967 --> 00:24:08,085
Now, each of our gun companies has
already ponied up $4 million...

372
00:24:08,247 --> 00:24:11,159
<i>...into</i> this Sportsman's Legacy Fund.

373
00:24:11,327 --> 00:24:15,400
Now that may not seem like a hell of
a lot of money where you come from...

374
00:24:15,567 --> 00:24:19,640
...but we think $20 million ought
to be enough to secure a jury...

375
00:24:19,807 --> 00:24:22,844
<i>...in</i> the People's Republic of Berkeley,
let alone here.

376
00:24:25,727 --> 00:24:27,319
How about 30,000?

377
00:24:27,847 --> 00:24:30,441
Thirty thousand, what are
you talking about?

378
00:24:30,687 --> 00:24:32,962
It's an interesting amount to reflect on.

379
00:24:33,487 --> 00:24:36,445
The number of gun deaths every year.

380
00:24:36,927 --> 00:24:39,282
The number of men, women
and children disabled...

381
00:24:39,447 --> 00:24:42,803
<i>...by</i> your gentlemen's products,
last year alone:

382
00:24:42,967 --> 00:24:44,639
"One hundred thousand."

383
00:24:45,127 --> 00:24:48,437
Or we could focus...

384
00:24:49,287 --> 00:24:50,845
...on the number one.

385
00:24:52,607 --> 00:24:55,679
Because one is all they want.

386
00:24:55,847 --> 00:24:57,963
One win. One precedent.

387
00:24:58,127 --> 00:24:59,401
Once they get that...

388
00:24:59,567 --> 00:25:02,764
...they're gonna be traveling around
filing civil actions...

389
00:25:02,927 --> 00:25:06,397
...and siphoning away
at that $2 billion...

390
00:25:06,567 --> 00:25:11,004
...that you gentlemen sell in firearms
and ammo every fiscal year.

391
00:25:11,167 --> 00:25:13,476
Two billion dollars!

392
00:25:14,487 --> 00:25:16,842
Where I come from,
that's a lot of money.

393
00:25:17,407 --> 00:25:19,682
What I'm asking for is a <i>pittance...</i>

394
00:25:19,847 --> 00:25:22,315
...compared to what
a negative verdict will cost.

395
00:25:22,487 --> 00:25:26,765
Our share price is down 25 percent
just on word of this trial.

396
00:25:26,927 --> 00:25:32,320
- I'm down almost 30.
- I'll kick in an extra 1.5, but <i>no mas.</i>

397
00:25:34,367 --> 00:25:37,643
One-point-five each, that's 7.5 total.

398
00:25:38,287 --> 00:25:40,596
- I'll take it.
- You have any additional plans...

399
00:25:40,767 --> 00:25:42,485
...for this pittance?
- I do.

400
00:25:42,647 --> 00:25:45,036
- Lonnie Shaver. Manager here?
- All day.

401
00:25:45,207 --> 00:25:46,879
- Ernie Strode.
- I'm gonna put <i>you...</i>

402
00:25:47,047 --> 00:25:49,607
...in the grocery business.
- Grocery business?

403
00:25:49,767 --> 00:25:51,405
We're acquiring your store.

404
00:25:51,567 --> 00:25:54,684
Meeting the managers to discuss
their future in the organization.

405
00:25:54,847 --> 00:25:58,362
<i>- He hasn 't been promoted in five years.</i>
- Not all will be transitioned.

406
00:25:58,527 --> 00:26:01,325
We've ID'd you as a candidate
for the Super House program.

407
00:26:01,487 --> 00:26:04,081
- How soon can we fly you up?
- Mr. Shaver...

408
00:26:04,247 --> 00:26:07,080
...in subtle and unspoken ways
can be made to appreciate...

409
00:26:07,247 --> 00:26:09,920
...the terms of advancement
in the Hammond Foods empire.

410
00:26:10,087 --> 00:26:13,557
- I don't like the looks of this one.
- Ex-Marine drill instructor.

411
00:26:13,727 --> 00:26:16,799
These people are looking for a leader.
They'll follow Herrera.

412
00:26:16,967 --> 00:26:19,640
- Lf they elect someone else?
- Whoever they vote for...

413
00:26:19,807 --> 00:26:22,560
...will be following me.
Just like in Cincinnati...

414
00:26:22,727 --> 00:26:24,285
...and Oakland and Pittsburgh.

415
00:26:24,567 --> 00:26:30,039
Gentlemen, trials are too important
to be left up to juries.

416
00:26:33,767 --> 00:26:36,565
God save this state
and this honorable court.

417
00:26:36,727 --> 00:26:38,957
Good morning.
You may take your seats.

418
00:26:39,127 --> 00:26:41,357
- Who's next?
- Herman Grimes.

419
00:26:42,527 --> 00:26:45,439
<i>- Is Herman Grimes in the court?</i>
<i>- Mr. Grimes isn 't on my list.</i>

420
00:26:50,007 --> 00:26:52,237
There's a swinging door ahead
of you, honey.

